'''硬式飛船'''（Rigid Airship）是指外形主要是以內建的框架來支撐住的[[飞艇|飞艇]]，次要的支撐則和[[軟式飛船|軟式飛船]]與[[半硬式飛船|半硬式飛船]]相同來自內裝氣體的壓力。<ref name="Mueller">{{cite journal|last=Mueller|first=Joseph B.|author2=Michael A. Paluszek|author3=Yiyuan Zhao|year=2004|title=Development of an aerodynamic model and control law design for a high altitude airship|publisher=American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics|page=2|url=http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA451761&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf|quote=In general, airships fall into one of two categories: pressurized or rigid. With pressurized models, the shape of the hull is maintained by a small pressure differential between the internal lifting gas and the external atmosphere. With rigid airships, the hull is formed by a lightweight skeletal structure with a fabric skin, while the lifting gas is stored in internal “gasbags”. The Graf Zeppelin II and the Hindenburg were both rigid airships. Pressure airships are sometimes made “semi-rigid” by adding a structural keel to share the bending loads generated from aerodynamic forces.|journal=|access-date=2014-07-27|archive-date=2012-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121002090612/http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA451761&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Konstantinov">{{cite journal|last=Konstantinov|first=Lev|year=2003|title=The Basics of Gas and Heat Airship Theory|journal=Montgolfier|publisher=AEROPLAST Inc|location=Kyiv, Ukraine|volume=1|pages=4–6, 8}}</ref>最著名的硬式飛船種類是[[齊柏林飛船|齊柏林飛船]]。
[[File:First_Zeppelin_ascent.jpg|thumbnail]]
硬式飛船盛行於1900年代至1930年代晚期，在興登堡號起火後開始退流行。

